## Skill-note usage rules

A skill note is a pre-entry learning artifact.

This Prep System file owns how skill notes are **used**.
**Building a Skill Note** owns how they are constructed.

### Governing rule

A skill note should make the learner stronger at:

- recognizing the pattern
- choosing the right representation
- explaining why the pattern fits
- and understanding the boundaries of the move

### Current live skill-note standard

During the current Alpha / Graybox phase, a skill note should contain only the educational foundation:

- **Problem Signatures / Recognition Signals**
- **Core Insight & Mental Model**
- **What this pattern does well**
- **What this pattern does not do / where it breaks**
- **Variant Map**

This top section is the core teaching object.

Interpretation rule:

If the top section is weak, everything downstream becomes weaker.
So the top section gets the highest quality bar.

### What does not belong in the skill note right now

During this phase, do **not** make the skill note carry:

- question ladders
- interview-quality problem lists
- optional harder reps
- “building upon the pattern” problem pools
- full worked variant sections
- large traces
- code archives
- decorative flavor framing

Those belong downstream in the quest or in later refinement, not in the active skill-note foundation.

### Why this matters

The skill note exists to capture the **soul of the pattern**:

- what it really is
- how to recognize it
- what it can do
- what it cannot do
- how its main mechanics branch into meaningful variants

Question curation should be built on top of that foundation, not mixed into it before the foundation is stable.

